-Yeah. my dad's a cop.

248
00:13:23.375 --> 00:13:26.292
-You're not gonna shoot anybody. right?
-Well. that's the plan.

249
00:13:26.958 --> 00:13:31.125
-Still. this could come back on you.
-If it does. I'll just say it was stolen.

250
00:13:32.500 --> 00:13:35.125
Here. Take it before I change my mind.

251
00:13:37.042 --> 00:13:39.208
Hate to press my luck.
but can you drop me somewhere?

252
00:13:41.042 --> 00:13:42.458
Anything else?

253
00:13:42.542 --> 00:13:43.792
[car alarm chirping]

254
00:13:43.875 --> 00:13:45.708
[ominous music playing]

255
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:54.708
We have a problem.

256
00:14:10.083 --> 00:14:11.375
[Williams sighs]

257
00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:13.250
Take a look at this.

258
00:14:16.375 --> 00:14:19.208
A woman with her daughters
at an amusement park?

259
00:14:21.292 --> 00:14:23.000
Is this another way for you to remind me

260
00:14:23.083 --> 00:14:25.792
that I should've taken you more places
when you were a little kid?

261
00:14:27.208 --> 00:14:29.875
Rachel Mills was carrying it
around with her.

262
00:14:29.958 --> 00:14:31.500
Maybe it means something.

263
00:14:32.125 --> 00:14:34.000
And yes. you should have.

264
00:14:37.917 --> 00:14:40.083
I pulled Hilde's phone records.

265
00:14:41.458 --> 00:14:43.583
Yesterday. she made a call
to a Boston number.

266
00:14:43.667 --> 00:14:45.708
Kyle Bergin. a career scumbag.

267
00:14:45.792 --> 00:14:47.500
Capo for the Fisher family.

268
00:14:47.583 --> 00:14:50.667
Kyle Bergin. aka Skunk.

269
00:14:50.750 --> 00:14:53.792
Armed robbery. multiple assaults.
racketeering. extortion.

270
00:14:53.875 --> 00:14:55.458
What. was this guy born mobbed up?

271
00:14:55.542 --> 00:14:58.000
He also had a couple murder charges.

272
00:14:58.083 --> 00:15:00.167
They were tossed due to technicality.

273
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:03.667
So. what is Hilde doing
calling someone like this?

274
00:15:03.750 --> 00:15:05.375
No idea. BPD is picking him up.

275
00:15:05.458 --> 00:15:07.875
and I'm having Hilde
brought down here so we can ask her.

276
00:15:07.958 --> 00:15:10.083
In the meantime.
I'm gonna take a last run at Rachel Mills

277
00:15:10.167 --> 00:15:11.625
before she's transferred to county.

278
00:15:11.708 --> 00:15:12.667
All right.

279
00:15:12.750 --> 00:15:15.958
And not for nothing. we all went
to Disneyland when you were nine.

280
00:15:16.042 --> 00:15:17.958
No. Mom and I went to Disneyland.

281
00:15:18.042 --> 00:15:21.458
You got as far as the hotel before
you caught a case and flew to Arizona.

282
00:15:21.542 --> 00:15:24.083
Oh. right. Yeah. the Browning escape.

283
00:15:24.167 --> 00:15:26.625
Well. we caught him
just outside of Phoenix.

284
00:15:26.708 --> 00:15:27.958
It was Tucson.

285
00:15:31.417 --> 00:15:33.792
I told David to meet me
at Washington Square Park.

286
00:15:33.875 --> 00:15:35.375
[police siren chirping]

287
00:15:36.375 --> 00:15:38.583
-[Skunk. on phone]What did you say?
-That I have answers for him.

288
00:15:38.667 --> 00:15:40.708
-You better hope he shows up.
-He will.

289
00:15:40.792 --> 00:15:43.500
Please tell Mr. Fisher
I did the right thing.

290
00:15:46.667 --> 00:15:47.875
Ms. Mills.

291
00:15:49.417 --> 00:15:50.583
How was your night?

292
00:15:51.208 --> 00:15:52.208
Pretty great.

293
00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:55.917
You guys should Airbnb this place
when you're not using it.

294
00:15:56.000 --> 00:15:56.917
Ha!

295
00:15:57.833 --> 00:15:58.708
That's cute.

296
00:15:58.792 --> 00:16:02.125
Sense of humor's key when you're looking
at 25 to life in prison.

297
00:16:02.208 --> 00:16:04.500
[Greer] Speaking of which.
I brought something for you.

298
00:16:04.583 --> 00:16:07.208
Thought you might want it
for your new cell.

299
00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:13.083
You wanna tell me who's in the photo?

300
00:16:15.417 --> 00:16:16.792
Just some friends of mine.

301
00:16:16.875 --> 00:16:17.875
Okay.

302
00:16:18.750 --> 00:16:19.917
Should I tell her?

303
00:16:21.292 --> 00:16:23.750
We spoke to Hilde Winslow
after David paid her a visit.

304
00:16:23.833 --> 00:16:26.250
She wouldn't speak to us.
but know who she called when he left?

305
00:16:27.500 --> 00:16:30.875
A capo in the Fisher crime family.

306
00:16:35.250 --> 00:16:36.083
What's up?

307
00:16:36.167 --> 00:16:38.958
So. BPD couldn't find Kyle Bergin.
so they asked us to ping his phone.

308
00:16:39.042 --> 00:16:40.792
-Great. Where is he?
-He's here in the city.

309
00:16:40.875 --> 00:16:41.708
What are you talking about?

310
00:16:41.792 --> 00:16:44.917
Cell tower puts him
at Washington Square Park ten minutes ago.

311
00:16:45.000 --> 00:16:46.833
and Hilde Winslow is missing.

312
00:16:50.333 --> 00:16:52.750
That capo Hilde called
is named Kyle Bergin.

313
00:16:52.833 --> 00:16:54.542
That name mean anything to you?

314
00:16:55.125 --> 00:16:56.875
Goes by the nickname Skunk.

315
00:16:58.667 --> 00:16:59.625
I've never heard of him.

316
00:17:02.417 --> 00:17:04.292
Let me explain something to you.

317
00:17:05.333 --> 00:17:10.250
Kyle Bergin is a problem solver
for Nicky Fisher himself.

318
00:17:10.333 --> 00:17:13.542
Now. if he catches up with David
before we do. it's not going to end well.

319
00:17:14.167 --> 00:17:16.000
Rachel. if you really wanna protect David.

320
00:17:16.083 --> 00:17:18.083
you gotta tell us
where he is before it's too late.

321
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:24.875
You know what? Fine. Call NYPD.

322
00:17:24.958 --> 00:17:26.792
I want Bergin picked up at the park.

323
00:17:26.875 --> 00:17:30.292
And put that one on a bus to MCC!

324
00:17:30.375 --> 00:17:33.083
[door opens and closes]

325
00:17:35.208 --> 00:17:37.208
[dramatic music playing]

326
00:17:40.750 --> 00:17:42.625
[indistinct chatter]

327
00:18:07.708 --> 00:18:09.292
[indistinct chatter continues]

328
00:18:21.333 --> 00:18:23.458
[dramatic music intensifying]

329
00:18:24.042 --> 00:18:25.208
Looking for someone?

330
00:18:25.875 --> 00:18:26.833
David Burroughs.

331
00:18:27.417 --> 00:18:29.000
Let's go. Skunk. Nice and easy.

332
00:18:31.292 --> 00:18:33.000
You had the old bird set me up.

333
00:18:33.083 --> 00:18:34.542
You know. I'm almost
a little bit impressed.

334
00:18:34.625 --> 00:18:36.792
You were such
a little bitch in high school.

335
00:18:36.875 --> 00:18:39.042
-Shut up.
-Always had Mackenzie fight for you.

336
00:18:39.125 --> 00:18:41.208
-Keep going.
-Hey. take it easy. tough guy.

337
00:18:41.292 --> 00:18:42.708
I'm just busting balls.

338
00:18:43.375 --> 00:18:44.708
[gasps]

339
00:18:44.792 --> 00:18:46.417
[people screaming]

340
00:18:55.083 --> 00:18:56.292
[grunting]

341
00:18:59.250 --> 00:19:00.500
[gunshot]

342
00:19:04.542 --> 00:19:07.042
[suspenseful music playing]

343
00:19:08.792 --> 00:19:10.417
[tires squeal. horn honks]

344
00:19:31.583 --> 00:19:33.333
[menacing music playing]

345
00:19:41.292 --> 00:19:43.292
[menacing music swelling]

346
00:19:56.667 --> 00:19:57.750
[exclaims]

347
00:19:59.833 --> 00:20:01.417
[groaning]

348
00:20:06.042 --> 00:20:07.083
Get up.

349
00:20:09.458 --> 00:20:11.875
[agent] Officers were on the way
when the shooting went down.

350
00:20:11.958 --> 00:20:15.125
Multiple witnesses say they saw Burroughs
arguing with another man

351
00:20:15.208 --> 00:20:16.708
before shots were fired.

352
00:20:16.792 --> 00:20:18.167
It's gotta be Skunk.

353
00:20:20.208 --> 00:20:21.625
[camera shutters clicking]

354
00:20:27.917 --> 00:20:28.875
Hilde Winslow.

355
00:20:30.083 --> 00:20:32.042
Driver's license read Harriet Winchester.

356
00:20:32.125 --> 00:20:34.417
-It's a long story.
-Which one of them shot her? Do we know?

357
00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:37.292
No. but we got a cell phone video
that was taken right after she was killed.

358
00:20:37.375 --> 00:20:38.875
-Let's see it.
-Officer.

359
00:20:38.958 --> 00:20:40.583
So Hilde helps Burroughs escape.

360
00:20:40.667 --> 00:20:43.917
then she calls Bergin.
and the three of them end up here.

361
00:20:44.000 --> 00:20:45.708
And then one of them shoots her?

362
00:20:46.917 --> 00:20:49.792
If Burroughs wanted her dead.
he would've killed her yesterday.

363
00:20:49.875 --> 00:20:52.708
If it was Bergin. the order definitely
came from Nicky Fisher.

364
00:20:53.542 --> 00:20:55.333
So how does Fisher fit into all of this?

365
00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:57.333
[agent] Here's the cell phone footage.

366
00:20:59.958 --> 00:21:02.125
[crowd screaming over video]

367
00:21:02.792 --> 00:21:03.917
[gunshot]

368
00:21:07.167 --> 00:21:08.417
Hmm.

369
00:21:11.125 --> 00:21:13.583
-Do we know which way Burroughs went?
-He ran south on Thompson.

370
00:21:13.667 --> 00:21:14.792
Chasing the other guy.

371
00:21:17.875 --> 00:21:20.542
Call MTA right now. Shut down the subways.

372
00:21:20.625 --> 00:21:21.542
What?

373
00:21:22.042 --> 00:21:25.917
After the gun went off. Skunk could've
shot Burroughs. but he didn't. Why?

374
00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:27.292
He just ran off.

375
00:21:27.375 --> 00:21:28.625
[Williams] Hmm.

376
00:21:35.083 --> 00:21:36.000
That's blood.

377
00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:41.083
Skunk's been shot.

378
00:21:42.458 --> 00:21:44.542
If that's true. he won't get far.

379
00:21:45.375 --> 00:21:46.667
[groaning]

380
00:21:47.917 --> 00:21:49.458
[panting]

381
00:21:51.583 --> 00:21:52.833
You're a dead man. Burroughs.

382
00:21:55.125 --> 00:21:56.875
I think you got us confused.

383
00:21:58.583 --> 00:21:59.708
Let me have a look.

384
00:21:59.792 --> 00:22:01.125
[breathing heavily]

385
00:22:01.208 --> 00:22:02.583
My wife is a doctor.

386
00:22:03.667 --> 00:22:04.958
Ex-wife.

387
00:22:05.542 --> 00:22:07.875
Gunshot like that.
you're probably going into shock.

388
00:22:08.500 --> 00:22:10.417
Now. I can get you an ambulanceâ€¦

389
00:22:11.667 --> 00:22:13.083
if you tell me where my son is.

390
00:22:14.667 --> 00:22:16.542
Revere Cemetery.

391
00:22:19.583 --> 00:22:21.542
-[flesh squishes]
-[groans and muffled screams]

392
00:22:21.625 --> 00:22:22.500
[cries out]

393
00:22:24.125 --> 00:22:25.958
[lift door buzzing]

394
00:22:34.708 --> 00:22:36.542
[police radio squawking]

395
00:22:36.625 --> 00:22:40.000
Rachel Mills.
JPATS to Metropolitan Corrections.

396
00:22:40.083 --> 00:22:40.958
Chopra!

397
00:22:41.667 --> 00:22:42.750
Hold up.

398
00:22:43.375 --> 00:22:44.375
Her lawyer's here.

399
00:22:44.458 --> 00:22:47.333
What? No. When did you make a phone call?

400
00:22:48.500 --> 00:22:49.500
I didn't.

401
00:22:55.083 --> 00:22:56.375
[clearing throat]

402
00:22:57.458 --> 00:23:00.250
I don't mean to sound ungrateful.
but who are you and what just happened?

403
00:23:00.333 --> 00:23:03.292
I'm your lawyer. I managed to get you
released on a million-dollar bond.

404
00:23:03.375 --> 00:23:05.750
pending an evidentiary hearing
of insufficient evidence.

405
00:23:05.833 --> 00:23:08.417
improper procedure. and lack of cause.

406
00:23:09.083 --> 00:23:11.708
So I'mâ€¦ free?

407
00:23:11.792 --> 00:23:12.958
Hardly.

408
00:23:13.042 --> 00:23:15.625
You're in a whole world of trouble.
just not today.

409
00:23:15.708 --> 00:23:17.958
Okay. well. you know
I don't have a million dollars. right?

410
00:23:18.042 --> 00:23:19.958
Yes. I gathered that.

411
00:23:20.583 --> 00:23:21.750
Soâ€¦

412
00:23:31.417 --> 00:23:32.458
Why am I not surprised?

413
00:23:33.708 --> 00:23:36.292
Whenever I really need you. there you are.

414
00:23:36.375 --> 00:23:37.625
What can I say?

415
00:23:37.708 --> 00:23:42.167
I'm like your own personal. wealthy.
incredibly handsome guardian angel.

416
00:23:42.250 --> 00:23:43.625
You left out humble.

417
00:23:43.708 --> 00:23:45.292
Add it to the list.

418
00:23:45.375 --> 00:23:47.208
-[laughing]
-[car starts]

419
00:23:47.292 --> 00:23:49.125
[traffic ambience]

420
00:23:50.333 --> 00:23:52.292
[Rachel] Wait. so how'd you know
I'd been arrested?

421
00:23:52.375 --> 00:23:54.042
Well. I went home to check on you.

422
00:23:54.125 --> 00:23:58.000
and I found David.
wearing one of my suits. I might add.

423
00:23:58.083 --> 00:23:59.083
He's innocent.

424
00:23:59.167 --> 00:24:01.958
Even if he is. it's not
a "get out of jail free" card.

425
00:24:02.750 --> 00:24:05.083
Look. you get caught with David.

426
00:24:05.167 --> 00:24:07.625
there's no lawyer in the world
that's gonna be able to help you.

427
00:24:07.708 --> 00:24:10.500
-I can't worry about that right now.
-You should.

428
00:24:10.583 --> 00:24:12.000
You need to walk away.

429
00:24:12.083 --> 00:24:16.417
I know. look. do you remember that guy
named Skunk who grew up with David?

430
00:24:17.292 --> 00:24:18.167
Okay.

431
00:24:18.250 --> 00:24:20.375
We saw him at the Fourth of July party.

432
00:24:20.458 --> 00:24:24.542
He works for Nicky Fisher.
and he's here in New York to kill David.

433
00:24:25.750 --> 00:24:26.792
What are you talking about?

434
00:24:26.875 --> 00:24:29.458
I know. it's a long story.
but I have to find him.

435
00:24:30.042 --> 00:24:31.292
I have to find David.

436
00:24:32.875 --> 00:24:33.958
What?

437
00:24:34.042 --> 00:24:36.500
I dropped David off
just before I came to get you.

438
00:24:36.583 --> 00:24:37.583
Where?

439
00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:42.292
Hayden. come on. please.

440
00:24:45.667 --> 00:24:48.458
[Greer] Skunk will wanna get
off the street and hole up somewhere.

441
00:24:48.542 --> 00:24:50.417
Well. the guy's leaking blood.

442
00:24:50.500 --> 00:24:54.417
It's not like he can just duck into a bar
or a restaurant and wait us out.

443
00:24:54.500 --> 00:24:57.333
Hey. Glenn. That's Glenn from
the Department of Transportation.

444
00:24:57.417 --> 00:24:58.958
You said there was
construction in the area.

445
00:24:59.042 --> 00:25:02.500
A stretch of paving on Mercer.
scaffolding on 8th.

446
00:25:02.583 --> 00:25:05.917
and an office renovation
on Thompson and Prince.

447
00:25:06.458 --> 00:25:08.458
Office renovation.
Are there crews there now?

448
00:25:08.542 --> 00:25:12.208
No. They ran into coding violations.
It's on hold.

449
00:25:13.000 --> 00:25:14.292
So the building's empty.

450
00:25:14.875 --> 00:25:16.667
Call tactical.
Have them meet us over there.

451
00:25:18.583 --> 00:25:20.500
[groaning and sobbing]

452
00:25:21.708 --> 00:25:24.750
You have no idea
what hell I've lived through.

453
00:25:26.292 --> 00:25:27.833
Or what I'm capable of.

454
00:25:28.583 --> 00:25:29.958
I'm gonna ask nicely.

455
00:25:30.708 --> 00:25:32.708
Why would Nicky take my son?

456
00:25:33.250 --> 00:25:35.125
[breathing heavily]

457
00:25:35.208 --> 00:25:39.792
Is this what you wanna be? You wanna
protect a man that kidnaps little kids?

458
00:25:39.875 --> 00:25:41.750
I thought you pieces of shit had a code.

459
00:25:42.625 --> 00:25:44.125
[screaming]

460
00:25:44.208 --> 00:25:47.917
Tell me why Nicky Fisher took my son.

461
00:25:48.667 --> 00:25:50.292
I don't even know him.

462
00:25:50.375 --> 00:25:51.333
Tell me!

463
00:25:51.417 --> 00:25:53.292
Ask your father.

464
00:25:53.375 --> 00:25:54.917
[Skunk sobbing]

465
00:25:57.958 --> 00:25:59.208
What does that mean?

466
00:26:00.458 --> 00:26:01.417
You heard me.

467
00:26:02.083 --> 00:26:05.833
You wanna know what Nicky Fisher
might have against you and your family?

468
00:26:06.958 --> 00:26:08.583
Ask your old man.

469
00:26:10.292 --> 00:26:11.208
Ask him--

470
00:26:11.292 --> 00:26:13.167
[police sirens wailing]

471
00:26:14.208 --> 00:26:15.833
[Skunk] Time's up. Burroughs.

472
00:26:16.500 --> 00:26:18.125
Even if you make it out.

473
00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:22.042
you ain't gonna last long walking around.

474
00:26:23.125 --> 00:26:24.833
[traffic ambience]

475
00:26:25.958 --> 00:26:28.875
You recognize any of the agents
that arrested you?

476
00:26:29.417 --> 00:26:30.625
Not yet.

477
00:26:30.708 --> 00:26:32.792
[suspenseful music playing]

478
00:26:32.875 --> 00:26:34.250
Shit. The coroner's here.

479
00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:38.292
Give me your phone.

480
00:26:40.583 --> 00:26:42.542
[sirens chirping and wailing]

481
00:26:46.958 --> 00:26:49.792
The whole world wants you dead. Burroughs.

482
00:26:50.458 --> 00:26:52.292
-Not just me.
-[cell phone vibrating]

483
00:26:53.417 --> 00:26:55.500
-Rachel?
-David. thank God.

484
00:26:55.583 --> 00:26:57.000
I'm here with Hayden. Where are you?

485
00:26:57.083 --> 00:26:59.667
I'm in an empty building two blocks south
of the park. There's cops everywhere.

486
00:26:59.750 --> 00:27:02.167
-I don't think I can get out.
-All right. we're on our way.

487
00:27:02.250 --> 00:27:05.333
I'm heading to an alleyway
with a bunch of construction equipment.

488
00:27:05.417 --> 00:27:06.875
Wait. we passed the renovation
a couple blocks back.

489
00:27:06.958 --> 00:27:09.042
Hey. meet us at the corner
of Thompson and Prince.

490
00:27:09.125 --> 00:27:10.125
[David] Got it.

491
00:27:10.208 --> 00:27:11.500
[tires screech]

492
00:27:11.583 --> 00:27:13.583
[tense music playing]

493
00:27:19.042 --> 00:27:20.292
[door bangs open]

494
00:27:23.292 --> 00:27:24.750
They're here.

495
00:27:24.833 --> 00:27:26.917
[tense music continues]

496
00:27:53.292 --> 00:27:55.292
[distant police sirens]

497
00:28:01.292 --> 00:28:02.125
On your left.

498
00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:09.958
You on the ground! Put your hands up!

499
00:28:11.792 --> 00:28:13.083
Do it now. Bergin!

500
00:28:15.958 --> 00:28:16.917
No sign of Burroughs.

501
00:28:18.125 --> 00:28:20.000
[menacing music playing]

502
00:28:22.458 --> 00:28:23.875
[Skunk breathing heavily]

503
00:28:25.125 --> 00:28:26.458
[officer]First floor clear!

504
00:28:26.542 --> 00:28:27.875
[sighs]

505
